<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Well for me I would go with stuns.  Breeze would be nice but it's a luxury not a necessity.  Mez would be nice but I don't use it a whole lot really.
<br />
What I do use is my stuns.  In a multiple mob encounter for example I'll cycle through the targets stunning them - currently daunting gaze, stupefy and overwhelming silence.  Actually I got the lvl 20 character ability version of overwhelming silence (Ghenna's something bolt or whatever) which is adept II quality.  It is such a great spell.  I can't tell you how much I love it.  For those that may not know it is a silence spell that disables special attack - or spell casting in the case of casters.  Grouping with my conjurer my stuns give him the ability to take down mobs he has no business taking down.
<br />

<br />
A recent scenario: 
<br />
I had a quest for foiling the bloodsaber plans from Captain Eitoa in Antonica.  At one point you have to kill a Bloodsaber courier which is a lvl 20^^ mob.  I was leading with Belldin so he triggered her and got initial aggro.  Before I could sic my pet on it he got hit with a crushing blow attack for 400 something dmg...nearly killed me (this was a couple lvls ago and before I went on a spending spree and upgraded my gear).  There's no way - as good as the hero pet is - that I'd be able to take him down with my summoner.  The pet heal is just too sucky and if I overnuked and got aggro then game over.  However, Belldin is so effective at dmg mitigation, silence - stun, stack some dots, throw another stun on when first wears off....killed him np.
<br />

<br />
It seems to me that our role isn't primarily CC like it was in EQ1, because there just isn't that much of it.  Sure we can put out decent DPS but that's more the department of Wizzys and conjurors.  IMO the enchanter benefits the group the most by dmg mitigation and therefore those type of spells is what I would upgrade.  Then again though you may have a different play style, so just go with whatever you cast the most I suppose.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
