<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">It seems pointless to me to upgrade stun spells. The only difference between app1 eerie focus and adept3 is the amount of mana it drains each tick. Personally I use Liskas Quietude (the lvl 40 specialization stifle upgrade) to drain mana and stifle of course. We have so many spells that drain mana from mobs why would i waste a ruby on a stun?
<br />

<br />
I think that the best spells to upgrade are our DPS spells. Despotic mind nearly doubles in damage between app1 and adept3. Despair goes from 60 per tick to 90+. Muddled Thinking hits for 193 at adept3 and at master1 it hits for over 200. Those are the spells that see the most improvement with upgrades, and thus those are the spell I upgrade first. 
<br />

<br />
After DPS spells I would consider consuming thoughts or devouring thoughts depending on your level. Stuns would be after that, or perhaps invis. 
<br />

<br />
Dont bother upgrading the breeze/refresh line. There no difference in mana regen, only in mana cost of the spell. Dont bother upgrading enthrall, there is no difference WHATSOEVER between app1 and master1. The take exactly the same mana and have the same duration.
<br />

<br />

<br />
just my 2cp.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
